.TH "i40e_ptp_write" 9 "i40e_ptp_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i40e_ptp_write \- Write the PHC time to the device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" i40e_ptp_write
.BI "(struct i40e_pf *pf "  ","
.BI "const struct timespec64 *ts "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pf" 12
Board private structure
.IP "ts" 12
timespec structure that holds the new time value
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function writes the PRTTSYN_TIME registers with the user value. Since
we receive a timespec from the stack, we must convert that timespec into
nanoseconds before programming the registers.
